xchange of blood carved out networks that made human populations into objects of medical surveillance and scientific research. Bangham reveals how biology was transformed by two world wars, how scientists have worked to define racial categories, and how the practices and rhetoric of public health made genetics into a human science. Today, genetics is a powerful authority on human health and identity, and Blood Relations helps us understand how this authority was achieved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBlood groupsxHistoryy20th centuryzEurope. 0aBlood groupsxHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aBlood groupsxResearchxHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aBlood groupsxResearchzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aBlood groupszEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aBlood groupszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aBloodxTransfusionxHistoryy20th centuryzEurope. 0aBloodxTransfusionxHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aBloodxTransfusionzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aBloodxTransfusionzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aHuman geneticsxHistoryy20th century. 0aHuman geneticsxResearchxHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aHuman geneticsxResearchzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  ablood groups.  ablood.  acollections.  ahuman genetics.  ainfrastructure.  apaper tools.  arace.  aserology.  atransfusion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and